# Skill Auto-Routing

Skills live in `.agents/skills/` and `.cursor/skills/`. **Do not wait for the user to name a skill.** Match the task to a skill, read its `SKILL.md`, then follow it.

## How Cursor loads skills (not manual)

1. **Rules** (this file, `ponytail.mdc`, etc.) — always in context
2. **Skill descriptions** — indexed; agent picks by task match
3. **Full skill body** — read on demand when matched (do not preload all 47)

Skip skills with `disable-model-invocation: true` unless user explicitly invokes them.

## BetterBox (project)

| Task signal | Skill |
|---|---|
| crawl, polish, translate, TTS, enqueue, worker, pipeline | `betterbox-pipeline-ops` |
| multi-file feature, PLAN, Codex handoff | `betterbox-implementation` → then **run** `request_codex_review.sh` |
| review, CODEX_REVIEW, before merge | `betterbox-code-review` (fallback if Codex down) |
| Codex/Claude handoff, ai-devkit | `multi-agent-handoff`, `agent-communication`, `agent-orchestration` |

## Engineering lifecycle ([addyosmani/agent-skills](https://github.com/addyosmani/agent-skills))

| Phase | Skill |
|---|---|
| Underspecified ask | `interview-me` |
| Rough idea | `idea-refine` |
| New feature / spec first | `spec-driven-development` |
| Break spec into tasks | `planning-and-task-breakdown` |
| Multi-file implement | `incremental-implementation` |
| Write/fix logic | `test-driven-development` |
| UI / React / CSS | `frontend-ui-engineering` |
| API / DB boundary | `api-and-interface-design` |
| Tests fail / debug | `debugging-and-error-recovery` |
| Pre-merge review | `code-review-and-quality` |
| Simplify working code | `code-simplification` |
| Security | `security-and-hardening` |
| Unsure which skill | `using-agent-skills` |

## UI taste ([taste-skill](https://github.com/Leonxlnx/taste-skill))

| Task signal | Skill |
|---|---|
| New landing / portfolio / marketing UI | `design-taste-frontend` |
| Redesign existing UI | `redesign-existing-projects` |
| story_reader pages | `design-taste-frontend` + rule `story-reader-nextjs` |
| Image → implement | `image-to-code` |

## Ponytail ([ponytail](https://github.com/DietrichGebert/ponytail))

Always-on via `ponytail.mdc`. On demand: `ponytail-review` (diff audit), `ponytail-audit` (repo audit).

## Conflicts

- **ponytail** (minimal) vs **taste-skill** (rich UI) — taste wins for story_reader UI; ponytail wins for Python pipeline
- **betterbox-code-review** vs **code-review-and-quality** — use betterbox for this repo's DB/queue focus; addy's for general review
